                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable N</hi> 104.) I received information that the prisoner had robbed his lodgings—I went to a house in Hackney-road, where a shoemaker lived, and found the prisoner—he denied himself to be the person—I took him into custody—he then said he lodged there, and had robbed the lodging.</p>
               <p>(The prisoner pleaded poverty. William Copplestone, of Brook-street, Clapton; Robert Taylor, of Nelson-street, Hackney-road; and Mary Summerford, gave him a good character.)</p>
